<item>
            <title>[JXPATH-83] JXpath automatically trims string values</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JXPATH-83</link>
                <project id="12310480" key="JXPATH">Commons JXPath</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When an xml contains a value with leading or trailing spaces, JXPath trims this value.&lt;br/&gt;
example: &amp;lt;value&amp;gt;     12324 56&amp;lt;/value&amp;gt; is retrieved by JXPath as : &apos;1234 56&apos; while I expect &apos;     1234 56&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12369462">JXPATH-83</key>
            <summary>JXpath automatically trims string values</summary>
